  "text": "Copaifera langsdorffii Desf. (Leguminosae-Caesalpinioideae) is popularly known as \"copaiba. \" It is a large tree that grows widely in Brazil, especially in Amazonas, Pará, and Ceará States [1] . There are previous published works using the hydroethanolic extract of C. langsdorffii leaves (Cop) for urolithiasis in rats [CITATION_1] , nephrolithiasis in rats [CITATION_2] , genotoxicity in mice [CITATION_3] , and carcinogenicity in rats [CITATION_4] .",
